<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>A Gem I am in Madrid often as part of my research in the Spanish Middle Ages. In addition, I direct a study-abroad program for US college students in Spain. All these activities keep me a Madrid regular. I consider the Hotel Moderno a gem of a hotel. It's impossible to beat the location: right off the Puerta del Sol, within walking distance of the Opera, the Royal Palace, the Cibeles fountain, the Prado, etc. Despite being in a busy area, the rooms are extremely quiet due to what seems to be some special sound-proofing glass on the windows. (But those on the front side can sill open up to enjoy a balcony overlooking Calle Arenal.) The bathrooms are magnificent: large, spotless, and some with marble floors and walls. The rooms are comfortable, with television, music, etc. I love the all-cotton, plush sheets. I've stayed in both single rooms (with a comfortable double bed) and doubles (with two individual beds). The buffet breakfast will satisfy the heartiest of appetites. The lounge on the second floor--simply, yet elegantly, appointed with sofas, chairs and occasional tables--is a great place to chat with friends. A real treat for me is having Wi-Fi internet access directly from my room and at absolutely no extra charge. I've gotten a bit spoiled and can't stand what I have to pay for internet service at some other hotels.One of the biggest plusses of the Moderno is the staff: attentive, genuinely friendly, and extremely knowledgable about sites and activities. After a couple of stays I began to feel like family--something that has made all the difference on quite a few trips back. And the prices are quite favorable--especially given Spain's on-going escalation in price. 
