<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>In the heart of magic Madrid! I booked this hotel for my partner and I as a surprise for his birthday. I chose the hotel after reading of it's location as it was important that we were in the middle of things. We certainly were! We got the metro from the airport to Metro Sol. This was amazing value! Took around 1hr 15 ish with a couple of changes and cost a mere 1 euro!!! We were astounded and very glad we didn't get a taxi, which most tour operators offer at æ‹¢40 each way! Don't do it unless you have walking difficulties ( there are steps at the metro stations like the London Underground but there are escalators for the deeper climbs!) We had concerns over metro safety but I felt completely safe! As long as you don't flash your cash and just be a bit aware of pick pockets (as with any city!) you will be fine.We had our map ready to try and find the hotel but as we came out of the Metro Sol, a few feet away was the Moderno! We checked into our room which was small clean and comfortable. The bathroom had excellent facilities (including a hairdryer). We had a veranda which looked out onto errr... a department store! But you didn't expect to see the sea did you? The windows had fantastic sound proofing! With the windows open it was very noisy, but shut you wouldn't know you were in the centre of this vibrant city! There is air conditiong so if you go in summer don't worry about having noise because you can keep your windows shut and turn the a/c on!The staff were friendly and you can leave your (bulky) hotel key with them when you are going out for the night. There is a safety deposit box which works by popping a euro coin in each time you wish to secure it so your belongings are perfectly safe.I would go on and tell you how wonderful Madrid is but it would take up a web page! Believe me, if you appreciate good food, culture, friendly people and long party nights...get on a flight now! 
