<Author>enjoytravel
<Content>Great Location Stayed March 18-20th with my 2 daughters. Very convenient location. We walked to the Palace, Cathedral, Plaza Mayor(great place for eating lunch outside with all of the entertainment--musicians, acrobats, mime type statues.....on a beautiful day!), Retiro Park, Prado. Be sure to wear your most comfortable shoes if you plan to walk to all the sites. My teenage daughter had a blister within the first hour from wearing the wrong shoes! Our room was small but very clean. 3 twin beds, marble floors and bathroom was all tile. PUll UP on the silver knob on the top back of the toilet to flush. I hadn't traveled Europe for awhile, it took me a minute to figure it out! HA! My daughters had a good laugh at me! When we checked in, they had us down for the wrong rate, they tried to say it was for the breakfast. I showed them a copy of my reservation--It didn't seem to matter to her(desk clerk) much..... My much less expensive rate INCLUDED breakfast.....Since my daughter has been studying there for several months, she knew a fair amount of Spanish, so she argued for me to get the rate we had booked thru the 800 domestic number. (the gal at the desk was not comfortable speaking English) We did not get it resolved the first day,which made me feel very uncomfortable starting the trip out, but when I checked out, the young gentleman at the desk that day, knew Engish very well, so it all worked out. I received my original rate.Breakfast suited us just fine---juices,fruit,coffee, pastries, interesting crackers, lunch meat, cheeses, jams, cereal---a glorified continental breakfast. The electricity is interesting. You have to put the key card (which is attached to the real skeleton door key!) in a slot to work the lights just inside the door. We had no air conditioning (they said it was still too early in the season for it to run), so the room got uncomfortably stuffy for all of us. UPon opening the window, the street noise was too much, (we were there on a friday and saturday night) so we had to close it again. (The revelers are out singing and talking loudly from midnight to 3-4am...)Great for a good laugh, but not for sleeping. (o: However, With the windows in the sleeping area closed, the noise does not penetrate--seemingly soundproof, so to get air ventilation, we had to open the bathroom window (no screens) since there was no air conditioning or fans. We slept quite comfortably then. Beds were very comfortable for us.I would stay there again because of the handy location and cleanliness. (The maids were washing the walls in the hallways!) Be prepared to pay for the nice location. You can get an English speaking desk clerk if you need it. The desk manager knows English if you have to straighten out your bill--you may have to ask for him. Just be sure and bring your Hotel confirmation letter, and please be kind. They were still quite kind to us, even though we had to argue the bill in the beginning. I was trying not to be a belligerant, demanding American when traveling to another country. We are used to having higher expectations, and I tried to keep in mind that I was a guest in another culture, where the way of living and doing things is different from what I'm used to. 
