<Author>PHNorthLondon
<Content>Perfect for my purposes For a single traveller, my smallish double accommodation was good size and superlatively equipped, with decor that was of high standard and clearly recent. E.g. solid dark-wood headboards and doors, fully-marbled bathroom, quality curtains and blinds and (I counted!) 16 beautiful mahogany-style coat-hangers. I presume I had a room which had been `done up' as some other reviews below sound very different.But of course the stand-out feature is the position, which is 20 metres from where they measure distances from in Spain! A thrill to walk out the door and be at the absolute the centre of everything -- starting with the amazing Mallorquina patisserie/cafe (open 8.00-21.15 daily) across the road which is a Madrid institution and hugely recommended.With early March nightime temperatures one obviously wants to sleep with the double-glazed windows closed, and on that basis no problem. Maybe it could be later. Otherwise the perfect choice and outstanding value. You'd pay at least double as much in (my native) London for anything remotely comparable. 
